                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The Learning Journey</h2>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <p>The 9-week program is divided into two main phases. In the first four weeks, learners explore the physics of motion through hands-on activities. They learn to use the scientific process as a tool to gain a better understanding of the connection between Mathematics and the principles of motion in Physics.</p>
                    <p>The program culminates in a student-organized event to raise awareness about an environmental issue. Each group of learners uses their understanding to build an interactive kinetic sculpture that demonstrates their concerns through a blend of art, physics, and creativity.</p>
                </div>
